handNote.note:
The script displays some relatively archaic features: the numeral ፮ has a compressed shape and the open loop; 
the letter መ has the loops not completely separated; the letters ፅ and ዕ and numeral ፬ show "cone-forms";
the word እግዚአ፡ ብሔር፡ is sometimes written as two separate words. 
The graphemes ግ and ዚ are occasionally written with ligature in the word እግዚእነ፡, e.g. on . 
One bottom ruled line has been left unwritten on leaves .

